04:20.140 --> 04:31.600
no professional help at all. And I began searching my library to see what editor
had published the majority of works and writers that I liked, figuring that we

04:31.600 --> 04:46.840
might have something in common as far as taste goes. So I began researching Don
Wollheim to see what his preferences were, where we differed, and where we were

04:46.840 --> 04:58.160
similar. And so I began to conclude more and more that we were fairly well
Simpatico when it came to taste. Not quite the same all the way down the line,

04:58.160 --> 05:13.480
but generally there's a broad area of overlap. So I found him very easy to work
